Package level

package level
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    ActorFactory
    The ActorFactory class provides a method for creating actor instances based on a given key.
    ItemFactory
    The ItemFactory class provides a static method for creating item instances based on a given key.
    KeyFactory
    The KeyFactory class provides static utility methods to interpret keys and extract specific properties such as color, picked-up status, open status, and direction for various game elements like items and actors.
    Layer<T>
    The Layer class represents a layer in a game level, containing a grid of objects such as actors, items, or tiles.
    Level
    The Level class defines and manages the structure of a game level.
    LevelReader
    The LevelReader class is responsible for reading and parsing level data from a file.
    LevelWriter
    The LevelWriter class is responsible for writing and saving the state of a game level to a file.
    TileFactory
    The TileFactory class is a utility class for creating instances of various Tile objects.
